ential psychotherapist Rollo May. This volume outlines the reciprocal influences of both thinkers by looking at the topics of fear, freedom, love, the demonic, power, and myth, and their significance for a contemporary examination of these topics.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 4aAngst. 4aFreiheit. 4aMacht. 4aMay, Rollo. 4aMythos. 4aTillich, Paul.  aMay, Rollo.  aTillich, Paul.  afear.  afreedom.  amyth.  apower.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z97831111757820 cEPUBz97831107806730 cprintz978311078032140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311078058140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110780581423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110780581/original  a978-3-11-117578-2  DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA5EBK